"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-pieter-coetze-fails-to-add-to-team-souths-medal-tally-breaking\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbPieter Coetze fails to add to Team South's medal tally  Pieter Coetze failed to add to Team South's medal tally at the Paris Olympics 2024 on Thursday night. Here's what happened \\u2026  Pieter Coetzefailed to add to Team South's medal tally at theParis Olympics 2024on Thursday night.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  Coetze finished a disappointing seventh in the men's 200m backstroke.  The 20-year-old Pretoria-born star stopped the clock in a time of 1:55:60.  Hungary'sHubert Kostook the gold medal.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  This breaking news story is being updated and more details will be published shortly. Please refresh the page for the fullest version.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzans